.TH stopntf 1M "August 3, 2001" "Sun Cluster 3.0"
.SH NAME
stopntf \- take the ntf server offline.
.SH SYNOPSIS
For network-aware (client-server model) applications:

.B stopntf
[
.B \-h
.I hostname
]

For non network-aware (client-less) applications:

.B stopntf
[
.B \-v
]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B stopntf
is a customized command that takes
the ntf server offline. Note that 
.B stopntf 
can only stop ntf servers created with the
.BR startntf (1M) 
command because
.B stopntf
and
.B startntf
use particular internal conventions for naming resources and resource groups.
.B stopntf 
executes 
.BR scswitch (1M) 
commands to do the following:
.RS 5
.TP 2
\(bu
Disable the ntf resource.
.TP
\(bu
Move the resource group containing the ntf resource offline.
.LP
.RS -5
.B stopntf
is idempotent, that is, you can call it
more than once without an intervening call to
.BR startntf .
.SH OPTIONS
.TP 12
.BI \-h \0hostname
If specified,
this optional parameter indicates the name of the
logical hostname or shared address
resource
used by the ntf server application to communicate with its clients
over the network.
.B stopntf
disables this network resource along with the ntf server resource.
.TP
.B \-v
Turn on verbose output to
print all the
.BR scswitch (1M)
commands 
.B stopntf
executes.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP 10
.B 0
Command completed successfully.
.TP
.B >0
Command did not complete.
.SH "SEE ALSO"
.BR scdsbuilder (1HA),
.BR removentf (1M),
.BR scrgadm (1M),
.BR scswitch (1M),
.BR startntf (1M)
